GATE H1: PASS (22 / 22)

Notable quality on Q1 and Q2 (client will not read applications without them):
- Q1 answer names lxml.etree.iterparse, elem.clear(), ancestor pruning, concrete
  numbers (80-120 MB streaming vs 600-800 MB full DOM), batch stream to PostgreSQL
  or S3. Code-level. The demo's memory chart is a live visualization of this answer.
- Q2 answer enumerates four concrete isolation layers: JWT tenant_id claim decoding,
  tenant-scoped SQLAlchemy session (automatic filter), PostgreSQL Row-Level Security
  with SET LOCAL (includes PgBouncer note), and API isolation test suite. Answers
  "at which layers" exactly as the client asked.

